name: Discovery Center
tweet: Titanic was one of the first ships in distress to send out an “SOS” signal; the radio officer used “SOS” after the traditional code of “CQD” followed by the ship’s call letters, via telegraph. 🛳️ #titanicdci  Titanic: The Artifact Exhibition opens 2/15!  https://t.co/Rwy5A4HZx5  https://t.co/WDpNUvFRCk

name: Gyanopedia
tweet: The first ship to send out an SOS signal is the Cunard liner Slavonia, having sent the signal on June 10th, 1909. It is a myth that the RMS Titanic was the first ship to use the SOS distress signal.  https://t.co/BUK5tuoNHi
